# No em dashes

**Never use an em dash** (the long dash character, Unicode U+2014).

This applies everywhere: user-facing copy, SPEC, comments, commit messages, PR descriptions, Cursor rules, and chat replies about this project.

## Use instead

| Instead of | Use |
|------------|-----|
| Clause break | Comma, period, or semicolon |
| Introducing a list or explanation | Colon |
| Parenthetical aside | Commas or parentheses |
| Ranges (years, pages) | "to" or a hyphen with spaces only when grammatically a compound modifier |

## Examples

```
Bad:  Pods start cheap — but costs climb fast.
Good: Pods start cheap, but costs climb fast.

Bad:  One method — bean-to-cup — wins on savings.
Good: One method, bean-to-cup, wins on savings.

Bad:  See hook 1 — lines cross on the chart.
Good: See hook 1: lines cross on the chart.
```

Before finishing any edit, scan changed files for U+2014 and replace every occurrence.
